                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/11–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé to the Czechoslovak Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-14T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 14, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. The Department will issue a warning to German authorities<note n="56"
                        xml:id="d812fn56">For text of warning, see <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>,
                        November 19, 1944, p. 596.</note> in line with your Zecho 22, November 7, 7
                    p.m., on November 15. OWI publicity will be arranged. British Embassy here
                    expects BBC to publicize similar British warning at about the same time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
